Scott Instruments Corp said ithas decided to concentrate on marketing new applications of itsexisting research.    It said it will realize cost savings from the reduction ofmanufacturing and marketing staff and overhead expenses.    The company said it will seek to license its Coretechs Vet3 speech recognition product to other companies and have themprovide manufacturing, market development, distribution andsupport activities in the industrial market.    It said it is near completion of talks for a Britishcompany to distribute Vet 3 in Britain and Europe. Reuter&#3;